<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870701-0086 </DOCNO><HL> Northern Telecom GetsJob With Turkish Agency</HL><DD> 07/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NT EUROP </IN><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Northern Telecom Ltd. said it signed an agreement valued at 360 million Canadian dollars ($270 million) with the Turkish Post, Telegraph andamp; Telephone administration for the delivery of digital telecommunications equipment over the next three to five years.    The telecommunications equipment maker said the equipment will support the manufacture of Northern's DMS telephone switching systems by Netas, a Turkish joint venture in which Turkish Post and Northern participate. The agreement is a continuation of a similar accord that began in 1983.    Netas is Turkey's leading supplier of digital telecommunications equipment. Certain Netas research and development programs are integrated with Northern. </TEXT></DOC>